clauses.clause:
The head of human resources is responsible for the following:


  Ensuring that an organizational classification oversight function is developed, implemented and maintained; 
  Identifying, assessing and prioritizing key organizational design and classification risks through oversight; 
  Informing the deputy head of potential risks and mitigation strategies in a timely fashion; 

    Providing the Office of the Chief Human Resources Officer with the following information when requested to do so: 


      Classification monitoring reports authorized by the deputy head; 
      Oversight information, such as departmental audit, performance evaluation and other similar reports related to the Classification Program; and


  Developing and implementing corrective action plans that incorporate and respond to feedback and recommendations received from the Office of the Chief Human Resources Officer, organizational audits or performance evaluations.
